```

---

# 🧠 WHY THIS STRUCTURE IS CORRECT

This structure separates runtime concerns into stable domains:

| Domain        | Responsibility             |
| ------------- | -------------------------- |
| `session`     | team/session identity      |
| `progress`    | navigation + traversal     |
| `inventory`   | quantity-based resources   |
| `flags`       | dynamic world state        |
| `stats`       | analytics/scoring          |
| `timers`      | runtime timing systems     |
| `rewards`     | reward ownership lifecycle |
| `checkpoints` | recovery/rollback          |
| `metadata`    | extensibility              |

This is a proper engine-state model now.

